<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-11-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-11-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="531" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d531">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">King of Italy</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">White
                                        House</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-11-16"><hi rend="italic">November 16,
                                    1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Your Majesty</hi>: I was gratified to receive your
                            telegram of the 30th ultimo, expressive of your appreciation of the
                            presence of the United States naval vessel <hi rend="italic">Minneapolis</hi> at the Genoa fetes.</p>
                        <p>It gave me great pleasure to manifest the cordial good will which this
                            government and people hold toward Your Majesty and the Italian people,
                            by directing the <hi rend="italic">Minneapolis</hi> to represent the
                            United States on an occasion to which Your Majesty’s presence gave
                            national interest and importance.</p>
                        <p>Your good friend,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Theodore
                            Roosevelt.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>